reference.title: Encoding for the L2 TLB
reference.shortdesc: The following section describes the encoding for L2 TLB direct accesses.

section.p: The following table shows the encoding that is required to select a given TLB entry.

row.entry:
Way
000 way0
001 way1
010 way2
011 way3
100 way4

section.p: The following table shows the data that is returned from accessing the L2 .

row.entry: Indicates that the entry is coalesced and holds translations for four contiguous pages
This bit field contains the valid bits for four contiguous pages. If the entry is non-coalesced, then 0001 indicates a valid entry.
